messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full HTTP path
- /v1/book

All methods acceptable
- False

Methods accepted for this path (based on the code)
- HEAD: False
- POST: True
- OPTIONS: False
- TRACE: False
- GET: True
- PUT: False
- DELETE: False
- PATCH: False

Explanation
- Blueprints composition:
  - app/__init__.py registers the v1 blueprint with url_prefix="/v1".
  - app/api/v1/__init__.py registers the book_api blueprint on that v1 blueprint with url_prefix="/book".
  - The create_book route is defined on book_api with route "" → full path is /v1/book.
- Routes present for that path:
  - get_books is decorated with @book_api.route("") and no explicit methods parameter — the code defines a handler for the path with the intention of retrieving a list (GET). This is the code-level evidence that GET is supported on /v1/book.
  - create_book is decorated with @book_api.route("", methods=["POST"]) — explicit code evidence that POST is supported on /v1/book.
- No code explicitly registers HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE, PUT, DELETE, or PATCH handlers for the /v1/book path. (There are PUT and DELETE handlers in this file, but they are on the different path /v1/book/<int:id>, so they do not apply to /v1/book.)
- "All methods acceptable" is False because the code explicitly registers specific methods (GET via the separate handler and POST via methods=["POST"]) rather than allowing every HTTP method.
